  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use groups when you need to reason about operations that can be reversed or about the symmetries of a structure.\n¶Definitions A group is a monoid (G,⋅,e)(G, \\cdot, e) in which every element has an inverse: for each g∈Gg \\in G there exists g−1∈Gg^{-1} \\in G such that g⋅g−1=e=g−1⋅gg \\cdot g^{-1} = e = g^{-1} \\cdot g.\nUnpacking, a group satisfies four properties:\n",
